name: éš†å®‰å‘å¸ƒ
description_trans: Long'an County is located in the southwest of Guangxi and is under the jurisdiction of Nanning City. Long'an symbolizes "prosperity and prosperity, long-term stability", and is also known as "Butterfly City" due to its butterfly like shape. Long'an County is 80km away from the center of Nanning and 70km away from the airport, belonging to Nanning's "one hour economic circle". Nanning Kunming Railway, Yunnan Guangxi High speed Railway (under construction), Nanning Baise Expressway and second-class highway, as well as Youjiang Waterway pass through. The territory is rich in natural resources, with Fenghuangshan silver ore reserves ranking second in the country. The main grain crops are rice and corn, and the economic crops include sugarcane, bananas, chestnuts, cassava, etc. It is known as the "hometown of Chinese chestnuts". Tourism resources include scenic spots such as Longhu Mountain, Lushui River Drifting, Xianyuan Valley, Buquan Scenery, Bangshan Wenta, Huidi Temple, and Yanjiang Old Street. The Dalongtan Stone Shovel Site discovered within the territory belongs to the late Neolithic cultural site, which is the largest group of large stone shovel worship found in the world. The wedge-shaped double shoulder large stone shovel unearthed from it has become the "treasure of the Guangxi Museum". In June 2013, Long'an County was awarded the title of "China's' Na 'Cultural Hometown" by the China Association for the Betterment and Progress of the People. The way to accept reports of illegal and harmful information: leave messages or comments in the background; Telephone: 0771-6529983; Email: larmt@qq.com .
